options.script:
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

def main(_):  # underscore since we don't use the parameter
    # Get date 60 days ago
    past_date = datetime.now() - timedelta(days=60)
    
    # Format the date as YYYY-MM-DD and return with endDate key
    return {
        "startDate": past_date.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    }

diagram_notes.content:
This Story enables you to use the ANY.RUN Threat Intelligence Lookup to retrieve detailed information on malware activity, including Indicators of Compromise (IOCs), OS event fields, threat classifications, and their interrelationships. This data is derived from an extensive database of interactive malware analysis sessions.

The Story supports two methods for submitting queries to the ANY.RUN Threat Intelligence Lookup:

- Form-based submission: Utilize the form located on the left side, which mirrors the functionality of the web interface available at https://intelligence.any.run/analysis/lookup. Enter your query in the provided text field, incorporating all necessary parameters, adhering to the required syntax, and including logical operators as appropriate.

- Webhook-based submission: Submit only the values (such as IP addresses, domains, hashes, or URLs) without specifying additional parameters or logical conditions. This method simplifies automation workflows. Note that hash values must be provided in SHA-256 format.

This Story automates obtaining indicator data from the ANY.RUN Threat Intelligence Lookup.

To use this Story, you need an ANY.RUN account with a "Hunter" plan or higher. Make sure your API key is added to your Tines credentials. 

ANY.RUN Threat Intelligence Lookup provides data about IOCs, OS event fields, threat classification, and relationships between entities, extracted from a large database of interactive malware analysis sessions.
Based on the results of the request to ANY.RUN Threat Intelligence Lookup, you will receive a notification indicating whether there are matches for the query or not.  

For more information about the ANY.RUN Threat Intelligence Lookup, please visit https://intelligence.any.run/docs
By default, the time period searched in ANY.RUN TI Lookup is 60 days

Upon completion of the query processing in ANY.RUN TI Lookup, a detailed report is generated if matches are identified according to the specified parameters.

The "Build Results" action extracts key elements from the report, including the threat level and the date of the most recent detection. Additionally, this action stores the complete source report in JSON format.

You can integrate this with other tools in your environment and develop automated workflows for threat response, leveraging the results from ANY.RUN Threat Intelligence Lookup. Finally, an email notification will be sent, containing all the details captured in the "Build Results" action.
